{{Top|leg}}
'''Jump pirates''' were organized [[Pirate/Legends|pirate gangs]] that assaulted [[Orbit/Legends|orbital]] [[Shuttle/Legends|shuttles]] as they passed through the topcloud layers, using antique [[Rocket pack/Legends|rocket packs]] from [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]] [[Rocket-Jumper Elite Advance Unit|rocket-jumpers]] to seize the [[Starship/Legends|ships]]. [[Atmosphere/Legends|Atmospheric]] bandits like these were particularly dangerous, since even a small mistake could cause their victims to crash from extreme heights to the surface instead of simply being marooned in [[Realspace/Legends|space]].<ref name="SWG:SJPL">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=terminal||Suspected Jump Pirate Lair}} on Corellia</ref>

When jump pirates sprang up more frequently on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] in the [[Time/Legends|time]] after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] and newsfeeds regularly reported about their actions, The [[Corellian Security Force]] placed special priority on stopping these thieves. CorSec also hired groups of heavily armed civilian investigators to check out suspected staging sites and destroy them if any sign of illegal activity was found.<ref name="SWG:SJPL" />

==Behind the scenes==
Jump pirates were mentioned in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Roleplaying game|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:SJPL" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> The Jump pirates were mentioned in the description of a mission called "Suspected Jump Pirate Lair", that was offered to players at [[W:c:swg:Mission Terminal|Mission Terminals]] on Corellia.<ref name="SWG:SJPL" />

